Add a newmoon number to a table that has the date

Source: R/prepare_moons.R
add_moons_from_date.Rd

Add a moon (newmoon number) column to a table that has a date (as a Date) column.

add_moons_from_date(df, moons = NULL, arg_checks = TRUE)

Arguments

df

data.frame with column of newmoon Dates named date.
moons

Moons data.frame. See prep_moons.
arg_checks

logical value of if the arguments should be checked using standard protocols via check_args. The default (arg_checks = TRUE) ensures that all inputs are formatted correctly and provides directed error messages if not.

Value

data.frame x with column of newmoonnumbers added.

Examples

 # \donttest{
  create_dir()

#> Establishing portalcasting directory at
#>  /tmp/RtmppX5q9A/file4ca251e6eebb/reference
  fill_dir()

#> Filling directory with standard content
#>  -Downloading raw files
#>   -PortalData
#>   -portalPredictions
#>  -Filling casts folder with files from archive
#>  -Filling fits folder with files from archive

#>   -AutoArima

#>    -exclosures

#>    -exclosures_interp

#>   -covariate data files
#>   -metadata file

  raw_path <- raw_path()
  weather <- portalr::weather("daily", fill = TRUE, path = raw_path)
  add_moons_from_date(weather, moons)
